The paper deals with the problem of reverse engineering of binary executables, which is a critical problem in computer security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes an end-to-end neural-based framework for code decompilation, which involves generating an abstract syntax tree (AST) and updating the code sketch using an iterative error correction machine guided by an ensembled neural error predictor. This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with code vulnerability analysis and malware detection, which are topics that fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also proposes a new approach to decompilation, which involves generating an AST and updating the code sketch, which suggests that it could belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
